Upload an externally built model that you’ve prepared. You can’t upload an externally built model in Hyperforce. Automated prediction writeback doesn’t support externally built models.

Before you upload, be sure to prepare your ZIP file according to Prepare an External Machine Learning Model to Upload.

In Model Manager, click Upload to launch the Upload Model guided flow.
Enter the model information, and then click Next.
Model Name	Unique name for this model. Required.
Description	Additional information about this model. Be sure to indicate that this model is external.
Model Type	
Regression (numeric use case)
Binary Classification
Multi-class Classification

Select the ZIP file containing the model files to upload.
Click Upload.

After the model is deployed, you can use it to derive predictions and improvements in Async Apex, Lightning components, Einstein Prediction Service, Einstein Discovery in Tableau, and bulk scoring. However, bulk scoring isn’t supported for multiclass classification models.

Deploy Models

To prepare your ZIP file, see Prepare an External Machine Learning Model to Upload.
See also: Upload and Deploy External Machine Learning Models
title: Uploading External Machine Learning Models
